-- Skidelsky Sees `No Obvious Path of Growth' in Europe
-- B y
-- 2013-04-15T12:24:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-15/skidelsky-sees-no-obvious-path-of-growth-in-europe-video-.html
Robert Skidelsky, a member of the 
U.K. House of Lords, talks about the outlook for Europe's 
economy, financial system and fiscal policy.  Speaking with  Tom Keene  and Sara Eisen on Bloomberg 
Television's "Surveillance," Skidelsky also talks about former 
Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher, who died April 8 at the age 
of 87 after a stroke. (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 03:36
 